task.summary: Add RevitBoundingBoxAdapter, update BoundingBox with factory method, implement clash detection command logic, and update project settings files.
Refactor `SlabsOpeningsCommand` to simplify logic, introduce `ClashDetectionCommand` for comprehensive clash handling, and update workspace configuration files.

feature: 1° Version with UI and commands works. Implement `ClashSelectionView` with corresponding ViewModel and integrate it into `SlabsOpeningsCommand` for enhanced clash selection and detection workflow. Update project settings and dependencies.

refactor: Simplify clash pane management by removing redundant commands and introducing `DockablePaneCreatorService`. Update `SlabsOpeningsCommand` to utilize new service for streamlined dockable pane handling.
refactor: Restructure namespaces and remove unused `RegisterClashSelectionPaneCommand`. Rename `App` to `ClashOpeningsApp` and streamline ribbon definitions to eliminate redundant button logic.

refactor: Remove obsolete domain entities, value objects, Revit API adapters, application interfaces, and associated commands. Restructure project, relocate resources to `src`, and update namespaces to align with new structure.

refactor: Rename classes, view models, and handlers from "ClashSelection" to "SlabsOpenings" for consistency. Introduce `ClassCollectors` for Revit-related data retrieval and update nullable references across handlers and view models.

feat: Introduce comprehensive clash detection and opening creation workflow.
- Added `ClashDetectionService` for clash analysis between linked models. - Added `FamilyPlacementService` for automated slab opening creation based on clash results. - Implemented `RevitElementCollector` and `ViewGeometryService` for element retrieval and search volume calculation. - Updated `SlabsOpeningsExternalEventHandler` and `SlabsOpeningsCommand` to utilize new services. - Removed obsolete `ClassCollectors` to streamline functionality.

feat: Enhance clash detection and opening creation process
- Refactored `ClashDetectionService` to include clash parameter extraction (`thickness` and `diameter`) directly in clash results. - Simplified `FamilyPlacementService` to work with enriched `ClashResult` objects, reducing dependency on pre-processed data. - Updated `SlabsOpeningsExternalEventHandler` and `SlabsOpeningsCommand` to use revised workflows. - Modernized `ClashSelectionView` with improved styles, layout, and responsiveness. - Adjusted dockable pane behavior to include new minimum dimensions.

refactor: Overhaul clash detection workflow and enhance consistency across services.
- Renamed several classes and services (`ClashDetectionService` to `ClashDetective`, `FamilyPlacementService` to `FamilyCreator`, `RevitElementCollector` to `ElementCollector`) for better clarity and naming consistency. - Updated `SlabsOpeningsExternalEventHandler` to align with revised clash detection and family creation logic. - Introduced `LinkElementData` for grouping link instances with their elements, simplifying clash detection process. - Improved error handling and localized user messages in `SlabsOpeningsExternalEventHandler`. - Modernized UI text in `ClashSelectionView` for better user interpretation.

refactor: Extract methods for improved readability and error handling in `ClashDetective`
- Introduced `ProcessElementPair` method to encapsulate processing logic for element pairs. - Added `AddClashResultIfValid` method to handle `ClashResult` creation based on clash parameters. - Improved error handling with explicit logging for debugging. - Replaced magic numbers with named constants for better code clarity (`MinVolumeTolerance`, `MinClashParameterValue`).

refactor: Improve modularity and readability in clash detection and family creation
- Extracted methods in `ClashDetective` for clash transformation calculation and improved processing element pairs. - Enhanced `FamilyCreator` by adding modular methods for family lookup and parameter setting. - Improved `ViewGeometryService` by splitting volume calculation logic into distinct methods for better clarity. - Updated localized error messages and refined transaction handling for better error recovery.

refactor: Add XML documentation and improve modularity across services and handlers
- Introduced XML documentation for better code clarity and maintainability in handlers, services, commands, and models. - Extracted multiple methods in `SlabsOpeningsExternalEventHandler` for better readability and modular processing. - Enhanced error handling and improved user feedback across commands and event handlers. - Added the new `RevitFamilyConstants` class to centralize Revit family and parameter constants, improving reusability.

feat: Add new minified architecture and diagram scripts for public site
- Introduced `architecture-I3QFYML2-2T2ZUHXO.min.js` for architecture module exports. - Added `architectureDiagram-UYN6MBPD-WBU2OYNU.min.js` to support diagram functionalities. - Included source maps for both scripts to aid debugging.

feat: Add new Revit project files for drilling, piping, and structural designs
- Introduced `Arquivo do Projeto de Furação.rvt` for drilling designs. - Added `Arquivo do Projeto de Tubos.rvt` for piping projects. - Included `Arquivo do Projeto Estrutural.rvt` for structural engineering.
feat: Add new Revit project files for drilling, piping, and structural designs
